{"id":"1609.02430","submitter":"Muhammad Sharif","authors":"M. Sharif and Iqra Nawazish","title":"Exact Solutions and Conserved Quantities in f(R,T) Gravity","comments":"24 pages, 3 figures, updated","journal-ref":"Gen. Relativ. Gravit. 49(2017)76","doi":"10.1007/s10714-017-2240-9","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.gen-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This paper explores Noether and Noether gauge symmetries of anisotropic\nuniverse model in $f(R,T)$ gravity. We consider two particular models of this\ngravity and evaluate their symmetry generators as well as associated conserved\nquantities. We also find exact solution by using cyclic variable and\ninvestigate its behavior via cosmological parameters. The behavior of\ncosmological parameters turns out to be consistent with recent observations\nwhich indicates accelerated expansion of the universe. Next we study Noether\ngauge symmetry and corresponding conserved quantities for both isotropic and\nanisotropic universe models. We conclude that symmetry generators and the\nassociated conserved quantities appear in all cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Sep 2016 07:57:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 May 2017 02:59:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-24"}
